<DOC><DOCNO> AP891208-0054 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-08-89 0614EST</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     12-08 0524</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0539</SECOND><HEAD>Snow Hits Arkansas, Plains</HEAD><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><TEXT>   Arkansas' first winter storm of the season dumped up to 3 inchesof snow, but much of the white powder was expected to melt todaywith temperatures rising into the 30s and 40s.   Snowfall was heavier in the West, where Story, Wyo., received 11inches of new snow. Sheridan, Wyo., recorded 5 inches Thursday.   Southern Kansas and Missouri also woke up to a snowy worldtoday, after a storm left more than a half-foot of powder.   Over 4 inches of snow fell on Syracuse, N.Y., by 12:30 a.m.today. The rest of the Northeast enjoyed generally clear skies.   A winter storm warning was posted today over parts of Virginia,West Virginia, Tennessee, Kentucky, Maryland, Delaware and NorthCarolina.   Snow advisories were in effect through this afternoon for muchof western and central Kansas, parts of Oklahoma and the TexasPanhandle into the state's northern plains.   Snow also was expected in south-central Ohio and in extremesouthern New Jersey.   A high-pressure front was expected over central Illinois thismorning. Arctic air over the region should trigger another round ofvery cold temperatures tonight.   Showers and thunderstorms threatened to produce heavy rain overthe central Gulf of Mexico coast. Flash flood watches have beenposted over southern Louisiana and southern Mississippi.   On Thursday, roads were ice-coated across the Texas Panhandle.An inch of snow fell in Amarillo, Texas.   The low temperature Thursday morning was 15 degrees below zeroat Warroad, Minn.   Temperatures around the nation at 3 p.m. EST Thursday rangedfrom zero at Warroad to 85 at Palm Springs, Calif.   Other reports at 3 a.m. EST today:   _East: Albany, N.Y., 05 fair; Atlanta 45 rain; Boston 15 partlycloudy; Buffalo 12; Charleston, S.C., 57 foggy; Chattanooga 41rain; Cincinnati 26 snow; Cleveland 22 cloudy; Detroit 20 cloudy;Hatteras 47 rain; Jacksonville 66 foggy; Key West 76 windy;Knoxville 40 rain; Macon 58 foggy; Miami 76 cloudy; New York 23cloudy; Philadelphia 25 cloudy; Pittsburgh 20 cloudy; Portland,Maine, 01 fair; Richmond 36 cloudy; Tampa 70 cloudy; Washington,D.C., 31 cloudy.   _Central: Birmingham 52 rain; Bismarck 07 fair; Chicago 17 fair;Denver 19 fair; Des Moines 19 snow; Fort Worth 33; Indianapolis 25cloudy; Kansas City 16 fair; Little Rock 31 freezing drizzle;Louisville 29 cloudy; Memphis 32 freezing drizzle; Nashville 32freezing rain; New Orleans 61 showers; North Platte 22 cloudy;Oklahoma City 28 cloudy; Omaha 21 cloudy; Rapid City 20 fair; St.Louis 26 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 05 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 09fair; San Antonio 41 fair.   _West: Albuquerque 30 fair; Anchorage 22 fair; Boise 33 cloudy;Casper 30 windy; Fairbanks 2 partly cloudy; Great Falls 37 windy;Honolulu 73 fair; Las Vegas 42 fair; Los Angeles 59 fair; Medford34 foggy; Pendleton 37 foggy; Phoenix 54 fair; Portland, Ore., 51rain; Reno 33 cloudy; Salt Lake City 33 partly cloudy; San Diego 56fair; San Francisco 52 foggy; Seattle 49 rain; Spokane 39 rain.   _International: Calgary 27 cloudy; Montreal 07 fair; Ottawa 03fair; Regina 21 foggy; Toronto 14 partly cloudy; Winnipeg 09 snow;Mexico City 48; San Juan 76.</TEXT></DOC>